His reign 
of terror finally ended in 1990 when he was caught red-handed with a 
six-year-girl hooded, bound, gagged and stuffed in a sleeping bag in the
 back of his van in the Scottish village of Stow. 

He had sexually assaulted her moments earlier.

In
 2012 he was prosecuted for a fourth murder, that of Jennifer, who was 
snatched as she cycled to a friend’s house in Ballinderry, County 
Antrim, Northern Ireland, in 1981.

The paedophile is serving a total of 12 life sentences for murder and kidnap.

Genette’s
 father, John Tate, told the BBC Radio 4 Today programme that he hoped 
police had not overlooked any other suspect by spending time focusing on
 Black.

