Police from different forces spent months trying to track Black’s movements in relation to various child murder cases.

They were able to say the former delivery driver had been spotted by Exeter airport - a short distance from Genette’s home village of Aylesbeare - and used petrol receipts to see where he had been travelling - but it is was never enough evidence to pursue a murder charge.

Tim Swarbrick, a retired Devon and Cornwall Police Superintendent, said: 'Cases like this are never closed. It would mean a great deal to the police and the community to see the mystery of Genette’s disappearance finally solved.'

Black was arrested by Devon and Cornwall Police in 2005 in connection with Genette’s disappearance but there was insufficient evidence to prosecute him.

